  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICCO Sierra Leone Ebola Response Project - Kailahun</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid aims to engage with and support EVD affected households and communities to reduce the transmission of the disease, meet immediate needs and mitigate the suffering caused by the Ebola Crisis.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Planned activities include,
1. Support 110 quarantined households have access to adequate and appropriate food, water and NFI assistance (reached 80 quaratined households wtih code 2, reallocated to project and 30 OVCs who were targetted instead of quarantined households)
2. Ensure 100 survivors have access to adequate and appropriate food and NFI and/or cash assistance
3. Reduced stigma and increase of support for Ebola sufferers and survivors</narrative>
  </description>
